{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":771,"text":"What's the fastest growing threat\nto Americans' health?"},{"time":4135,"text":"Cancer? Heart attacks? Diabetes?"},{"time":7603,"text":"The answer is actually none of these;"},{"time":9449,"text":"it's Alzheimer's disease."},{"time":11250,"text":"Every 67 seconds,"},{"time":13276,"text":"someone in the United States\nis diagnosed with Alzheimer's."},{"time":16761,"text":"As the number of Alzheimer's patients\ntriples by the year 2050,"},{"time":20149,"text":"caring for them, as well as\nthe rest of the aging population,"},{"time":23446,"text":"will become an overwhelming\nsocietal challenge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26585,"text":"My family has experienced firsthand"},{"time":28465,"text":"the struggles of caring\nfor an Alzheimer's patient."},{"time":30967,"text":"Growing up in a family\nwith three generations,"},{"time":33107,"text":"I've always been very close\nto my grandfather."},{"time":35262,"text":"When I was four years old,"},{"time":36689,"text":"my grandfather and I \nwere walking in a park in Japan"},{"time":39192,"text":"when he suddenly got lost."},{"time":40497,"text":"It was one of the scariest moments\nI've ever experienced in my life,"},{"time":43710,"text":"and it was also the first\ninstance that informed us"},{"time":46117,"text":"that my grandfather\nhad Alzheimer's disease."},{"time":48682,"text":"Over the past 12 years,\nhis condition got worse and worse,"},{"time":52025,"text":"and his wandering in particular\ncaused my family a lot of stress."},{"time":55823,"text":"My aunt, his primary caregiver,"},{"time":57302,"text":"really struggled to stay awake at night\nto keep an eye on him,"},{"time":60349,"text":"and even then often failed\nto catch him leaving the bed."},{"time":63047,"text":"I became really concerned\nabout my aunt's well-being"},{"time":65858,"text":"as well as my grandfather's safety."},{"time":67599,"text":"I searched extensively for a solution\nthat could help my family's problems,"},{"time":71130,"text":"but couldn't find one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72960,"text":"Then, one night about two years ago,"},{"time":75693,"text":"I was looking after my grandfather\nand I saw him stepping out of the bed."},{"time":79158,"text":"The moment his foot landed on the floor,"},{"time":81150,"text":"I thought, why don't I put\na pressure sensor on the heel of his foot?"},{"time":84412,"text":"Once he stepped onto the floor\nand out of the bed,"},{"time":86809,"text":"the pressure sensor would detect an\nincrease in pressure caused by body weight"},{"time":90516,"text":"and then wirelessly send an audible alert\nto the caregiver's smartphone."},{"time":93971,"text":"That way, my aunt could sleep\nmuch better at night"},{"time":96312,"text":"without having to worry\nabout my grandfather's wandering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99002,"text":"So now I'd like to perform\na demonstration of this sock."},{"time":105134,"text":"Could I please have\nmy sock model on the stage?"},{"time":108831,"text":"Great."},{"time":112170,"text":"So once the patient\nsteps onto the floor --"},{"time":115950,"text":"(Ringing) --"},{"time":117510,"text":"an alert is sent\nto the caregiver's smartphone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124571,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":126057,"text":"Thank you, sock model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132045,"text":"So this is a drawing\nof my preliminary design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135819,"text":"My desire to create\na sensor-based technology"},{"time":138441,"text":"perhaps stemmed from my lifelong love\nfor sensors and technology."},{"time":141979,"text":"When I was six years old,"},{"time":143465,"text":"an elderly family friend\nfell down in the bathroom"},{"time":145795,"text":"and suffered severe injuries."},{"time":147505,"text":"I became concerned\nabout my own grandparents"},{"time":149606,"text":"and decided to invent\na smart bathroom system."},{"time":151958,"text":"Motion sensors would be installed\ninside the tiles of bathroom floors"},{"time":155566,"text":"to detect the falls of elderly patients\nwhenever they fell down in the bathroom."},{"time":159404,"text":"Since I was only six years old at the time"},{"time":161416,"text":"and I hadn't graduated\nfrom kindergarten yet,"},{"time":163739,"text":"I didn't have the necessary resources and \ntools to translate my idea into reality,"},{"time":168073,"text":"but nonetheless, my research experience"},{"time":170706,"text":"really implanted in me a firm desire\nto use sensors to help the elderly people."},{"time":174957,"text":"I really believe that sensors can improve\nthe quality of life of the elderly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180944,"text":"When I laid out my plan, I realized\nthat I faced three main challenges:"},{"time":184425,"text":"first, creating a sensor;"},{"time":186194,"text":"second, designing a circuit;"},{"time":187773,"text":"and third, coding a smartphone app."},{"time":189519,"text":"This made me realize that my project\nwas actually much harder to realize"},{"time":192927,"text":"than I initially had thought it to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194982,"text":"First, I had to create a wearable sensor\nthat was thin and flexible enough\n"},{"time":198476,"text":"to be worn comfortably\non the bottom of the patient's foot."},{"time":201237,"text":"After extensive research and testing\nof different materials like rubber,"},{"time":204656,"text":"which I realized was too thick to be worn\nsnugly on the bottom of the foot,"},{"time":208191,"text":"I decided to print a film sensor"},{"time":209758,"text":"with electrically conductive\npressure-sensitive ink particles."},{"time":212660,"text":"Once pressure is applied, the connectivity\nbetween the particles increases."},{"time":216236,"text":"Therefore, I could design a circuit\nthat would measure pressure"},{"time":219200,"text":"by measuring electrical resistance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221267,"text":"Next, I had to design\na wearable wireless circuit,"},{"time":224026,"text":"but wireless signal transmission\nconsumes lots of power"},{"time":227338,"text":"and requires heavy, bulky batteries."},{"time":229101,"text":"Thankfully, I was able to find out\nabout the Bluetooth low energy technology,"},{"time":232728,"text":"which consumes very little power\nand can be driven by a coin-sized battery."},{"time":236251,"text":"This prevented the system\nfrom dying in the middle of the night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239880,"text":"Lastly, I had to code a smartphone app\nthat would essentially transform"},{"time":243343,"text":"the care-giver's smartphone\ninto a remote monitor."},{"time":245821,"text":"For this, I had to expand upon\nmy knowledge of coding with Java and XCode"},{"time":249497,"text":"and I also had to learn about how to code\nfor Bluetooth low energy devices"},{"time":252984,"text":"by watching YouTube tutorials\nand reading various textbooks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257230,"text":"Integrating these components, I was able\nto successfully create two prototypes,"},{"time":261019,"text":"one in which the sensor\nis embedded inside a sock,"},{"time":263347,"text":"and another that's\na re-attachable sensor assembly"},{"time":265743,"text":"that can be adhered anywhere\nthat makes contact"},{"time":267949,"text":"with the bottom of the patient's foot."},{"time":269782,"text":"I've tested the device on my grandfather\nfor about a year now,"},{"time":272682,"text":"and it's had a 100 percent success rate"},{"time":274593,"text":"in detecting the over 900 \nknown cases of his wandering."},{"time":278629,"text":"Last summer, I was able\nto beta test my device"},{"time":281052,"text":"at several residential\ncare facilities in California,"},{"time":283598,"text":"and I'm currently incorporating\nthe feedback"},{"time":285770,"text":"to further improve the device \ninto a marketable product."},{"time":288733,"text":"Testing the device on a number of patients"},{"time":290841,"text":"made me realize that I needed\nto invent solutions"},{"time":293350,"text":"for people who didn't want\nto wear socks to sleep at night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296805,"text":"So sensor data, collected\non a vast number of patients,"},{"time":299630,"text":"can be useful for improving patient care"},{"time":301959,"text":"and also leading to a cure\nfor the disease, possibly."},{"time":304777,"text":"For example, I'm currently examining \n"},{"time":306620,"text":"correlations between the frequency\nof a patient's nightly wandering"},{"time":309848,"text":"and his or her daily activities and diet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313854,"text":"One thing I'll never forget\nis when my device first caught"},{"time":316615,"text":"my grandfather's wandering\nout of bed at night."},{"time":318833,"text":"At that moment, I was really struck\nby the power of technology"},{"time":321784,"text":"to change lives for the better."},{"time":324011,"text":"People living happily and healthfully --"},{"time":326131,"text":"that's the world that I imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328156,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330216,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}